[thinking] **Evaluating Java 17 Class Definition**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering if defining a class in the same package within an unnamed module is allowed, especially if another code source defines the package. I think ClassLoader's defineClass method checks the code source for packages — but what if the Javassist bytes have a null code source? Maybe I could leverage the protection domain to match using ClassPool.class.getProtectionDomain(). I'm noting that the existing toClass method uses a test protection domain. This needs more clarity!
