[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering interface visibility**\n\nI'm thinking about whether I need to make this interface public. There’s the option of having a nested public interface, but I need to weigh the pros and cons of visibility. I should consider what kind of accessibility is required and if making it public adds value to its usability. It’s like deciding if sharing a tool with everyone is worth it — will it lead to better outcomes or just more confusion?\n\n**Evaluating Java 17 Class Definition**\n\nI'm wondering if defining a class in the same package within an unnamed module is allowed, especially if another code source defines the package. I think ClassLoader's defineClass method checks the code source for packages — but what if the Javassist bytes have a null code source? Maybe I could leverage the protection domain to match using ClassPool.class.getProtectionDomain(). I'm noting that the existing toClass method uses a test protection domain. This needs more clarity!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_053294151caacb700169f9eac926cc8190b1ca51b9b3ad48ad\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-eraqkYMdw7rBTDYF7c7l-9UThEdz-K23hCCnbeDsCxpM04ps8nPdmdP-7MGw23s__hkcgAfvBGvinroQLAXV64EO0smzhsAVou0-X22tm5gyXlWwVd1G7ZEjNEldL_ORYeobrP6uFtrsGLqwH8GOYDZNLMQ9FneCJ0fNaIYLyNagqA7gsjPWGVg-kSx5592VCGeDbFfmWs8eiQDpOXLQGiHS8Y2gtoru-wiyxicyYmupjP-FXVI5yCus-CnkUlt-XXhDtmM6oZY1_7MEJqVvp1E_iCejt3PBKoEgD7XCKf4xu8u-rBdSeYsA68K8TnZQcZyxXQZCAC4zJVMG9TxXzQ49-_mHIz3TditRHCypwK2Z_hQkeWOABhJJDRF8rYnjInNqloh66uu0_mfyugboB5Ywom-KuWrp6eJdWOj_-GD82yAbfyxFnAaCu3Ie41w5hy_cGWkQELx_bnhSNOGAnd9t5P6FhCaMSu-oSO2000qdnnNDFp6uwCwr_mWY6RkSPqdvvisxCYgEm7tpEdgQIX3Yd1Ok1HMNm4wvh82xZuIsQSx05Bv2qUDfOx1K2EljOlMKBk8I7AwF2iZ9yA2WqgCpi6AM2bLekUfdNHtKVjkhaFSyCSz8xPLhIKtYqv7fg8xto9vM2LDinhKxO0rpxHFfDQ_maMUENAz63o_ZLCMZfHKRkwBRuu6cuedlzRO6DgjDeQFr75gXH10nZjHwJ3elcs9fGEQ9e0hv3OaocWbKtu-KxdgL5wCV758OAMVRxpSMIhP