lity**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether I need to make this interface public. There’s the option of having a nested public interface, but I need to weigh the pros and cons of visibility. I should consider what kind of accessibility is required and if making it public adds value to its usability. It’s like deciding if sharing a tool with everyone is worth it — will it lead to better outcomes or just more confusion?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java 17 Class Definition**\\n\\nI'm wondering if defining a class in the same package within an unnamed module is allowed, especially if another code source defines the package. I think ClassLoader's defineClass method checks the code source for packages — but what if the Javassist bytes have a null code source? Maybe I could leverage the protection domain to match using ClassPool.class.getProtectionDomain(). I'm noting that the existing toClass method uses a test protection domain. This needs more clarity!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pXqtv1152rr3P6HNO6EbwYTg|fc_053294151caacb700169f9eadacfe88190bb9024dd8c901a67", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/ClassPoolTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n", "newText": "import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n"}, {"oldText": "import javassist.CtClass;\n", "newText": "import javassist.CtClass;\nimport javassist.CtNewMethod;\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final String CLASS_POOL_HELPER_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist.ClassPool$1\";\n    private static final AtomicInteger CLASS_COUNTER = new AtomicInteger();\n\n    @Test\n    void isolatedClassLoadingInitializesClassPoolStaticDefineClassMethods() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            IsolatedClassPoolLoader isolatedLoader = new IsolatedClassPoolLoader();\n            Class<?> isolatedClassPool = Class.forName(\n                    ClassPool.class.getName(),\n                    true,\n                    isolatedLoader);\n\n            assertThat(isolatedClassPool.getName()).isEqualTo(ClassPool.class.getName());\n            assertThat(isolatedClassPool.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(isolatedLoader);\n        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n\n", "newText": "    private static final AtomicInteger CLASS_COUNTER = new AtomicInteger();\n\n    @Test\n    void generatedSamePackageInvokerCallsSyntheticClassLiteralHelper() throws Exception {\n        ClassPool pool = new ClassPool(true);\n        CtClass generatedClass = pool.makeClass(nextClassPoolPackageClassName());\n        generatedClass.addInterface(pool.get(ClassResolver.class.getName()));\n        generatedClass.addMethod(CtNewMethod.make(\"\"\"\n                public java.lang.Class resolve(String name) {\n                    return javassist.ClassPool.class$(name);\n                }\n                \"\"\", generatedClass));\n\n        try {\n            Class<?> loadedClass = pool.toClass(\n                    generatedClass,\n                    ClassPool.class.getClassLoader(),\n                    ClassPool.class.getProtectionDomain());\n            ClassResolver resolver = (ClassResolver) loadedClass.getDeclaredConstructor().newInstance();\n\n            assertThat(resolver.resolve(String.class.getName())).isSameAs(String.class);\n        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            rethrowIfNotUnsupportedFeatureError(throwable);\n        } finally {\n            generatedClass.detach();\n        }\n    }\n\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static String nextGeneratedClassName() {\n        return ClassPoolTest.class.getPackageName()\n                + \".ClassPoolGenerated\"\n                + CLASS_COUNTER.incrementAndGet();\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static String nextGeneratedClassName() {\n        return ClassPoolTest.class.getPackageName()\n                + \".ClassPoolGenerated\"\n                + CLASS_COUNTER.incrementAndGet();\n    }\n\n    private static String nextClassPoolPackageClassName() {\n        return ClassPool.class.getPackageName()\n                + \".ClassPoolHelperInvoker\"\n                + CLASS_COUNTER.incrementAndGet();\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class IsolatedClassPoolLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private IsolatedClassPoolLoader() {\n            super(ClassPoolTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null && shouldLoadIsolated(name)) {\n                    loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                } else if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = super.loadClass(name, false);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!shouldLoadIsolated(name)) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n            }\n            byte[] bytes = readClassBytes(name);\n            return defineClass(name, bytes, 0, bytes.length);\n        }\n\n        private boolean shouldLoadIsolated(String name) {\n            return ClassPool.class.getName().equals(name)\n                    || CLASS_POOL_HELPER_CLASS_NAME.equals(name);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] readClassBytes(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream input = getParent().getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (input == null) {\n                    return new byte[0];\n                }\n                return input.readAllBytes();\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name, exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n", "newText": "    public interface ClassResolver {\n        Class<?> resolve(String name);\n    }\n\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2893, "output": 2468, "cacheRead": 42496, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47857, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777986247622, "responseId": "resp_053294151caacb700169f9eac84e048190863ae543889b4304"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_pXqtv1152rr3P6HNO6EbwYTg|fc_053294151caacb700169f9eadacfe88190bb9024dd8c901a67", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 5 block(s) in tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/ClassPoolTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   7 package javassist.javassist;\n   8 \n   9 import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n  10 \n- 11 import java.io.IOException;\n- 12 import java.io.InputStream;\n  13 import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n  14 \n  15 import javassist.ClassPool;\n  16 import javassist.CtClass;\n+ 15 import javassist.CtNewMethod;\n  17 import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\n  18 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n  19 \n  20 public class ClassPoolTest {\n- 21     private static final String CLASS_POOL_HELPER_CLASS_NAME = \"javassist.ClassPool$1\";\n  22     private static final AtomicInteger CLASS_COUNTER = new AtomicInteger();\n  23 \n  24     @Test\n- 25     void isolatedClassLoadingInitializesClassPoolStaticDefineClassMethods() throws Exception {\n+ 23     void generatedSamePackageInvokerCallsSyntheticClassLiteralHelper(